CRC Card
Class: DataReceiver
Responsibilities:
•	Receive incoming aircraft transponder data
•	Check that received data is not obviously corrupted
•	Pass valid data to be stored/updated in the system
Collaborators (if any):
•	AircraftDatabase
Assumptions (if any):
•	Data already comes in a standard format understood by this system
•	Corrupted data can be detected in a simple way
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRC Card
Class: Aircraft
Responsibilities:
•	Store current information about a single aircraft (ID, type, position, speed, altitude, heading)
•	Update its stored information when new data arrives
•	Provide its information to other parts of the system when requested

Collaborators (if any):
•	AircraftDatabase
Assumptions (if any):
•	Each aircraft has a unique identifier in the received data
•	Only the latest state is needed for this assignment (no detailed history)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRC Card
Class: AircraftDatabase
Responsibilities:
•	Keep a collection of all currently tracked Aircraft
•	Add new Aircraft when a new ID appears
•	Update existing Aircraft with new data from the receiver
•	Find Aircraft by ID for queries and display
•	Provide a list of all Aircraft for display and safety checks
Collaborators:
•	TransponderReceiver
•	Aircraft
•	ConflictDetector
•	ControllerQueryHandler
•	GraphicsDisplay
Assumptions:
•	Everything fits in memory for this small airport
•	Old Aircraft are removed using some simple rule (e.g., no data for a while)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRC Card
Class: GraphicsDisplay
Responsibilities:
•	Draw all aircraft on the controller’s screen using the supplied view data
•	Every 10 seconds, read all Aircraft from the database
•	Build a simple view model (position and basic info) for the screen
•	Show labels and basic flight info near each aircraft symbol
•	Visually highlight aircraft that are in a dangerous situation
Collaborators:
•	ConflictDetector
Assumptions:
•	There is an existing UI framework to handle the actual drawing
•	Highlighting rules (color, blinking) are defined elsewhere
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRC Card
Class: ConflictDetector
Responsibilities:
•	Periodically analyze aircraft in the database for dangerous situations
•	Detect pairs (or small groups) of aircraft that are too close or converging
•	Mark or record which aircraft are in conflict so the display can show them
Collaborators (if any):
•	AircraftDatabase
•	Aircraft
•	GraphicsDisplay
Assumptions (if any):
•	Simple distance/altitude rules are enough to decide “dangerous”
•	Checking can be done often enough to be useful (e.g., on each display update)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CRC Card
Class: ControllerQueryHandler
Responsibilities:
•	Handle controller requests for more details about a specific aircraft
•	Look up the requested aircraft in the database
•	Return formatted details for display in a details panel or popup
Collaborators (if any):
•	AircraftDatabase
•	Aircraft
Assumptions (if any):
•	The controller can choose an aircraft (e.g., by ID or clicking on the screen)
•	There is some UI element to show the detailed information


